<ServicePage
  name="Tree Removal"
  slug="tree-removal"
  headline="Tree Removal in Concord, NC"
  intro="Safe, efficient tree removal for residential and commercial properties throughout Cabarrus County. Any size tree, any location."
  priceRange="$300 – $2,500+"
  benefits={[
    'Licensed & fully insured',
    'Any size tree — any location',
    'Safe removal near structures & power lines',
    'Complete debris cleanup included',
    'Free on-site estimates',
    'Same-day emergency service',
  ]}
  body={`
    <h2>Professional Tree Removal You Can Trust</h2>
    <p>Dead, dying, or hazardous trees are more than an eyesore — they're a liability. A single storm can turn a weakened tree into thousands of dollars in property damage. Our crew handles the full tree removal process from assessment to cleanup, using professional-grade equipment and proven rigging techniques.</p>

    <h2>When Does a Tree Need to Be Removed?</h2>
    <p>Not every tree needs to come down. But if you notice any of these warning signs, it's time to call a professional:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Dead or dying branches in the crown</li>
      <li>Visible trunk damage, cracks, or cavities</li>
      <li>Leaning that's gotten worse over time</li>
      <li>Roots lifting out of the ground</li>
      <li>Fungal growth at the base or on the trunk</li>
      <li>Proximity to your home, garage, or power lines</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Tree Removal Process</h2>
    <p>Every job starts with a free on-site assessment. We evaluate the tree's condition, size, location, and any obstacles (power lines, fences, structures). Then we provide a flat-rate quote — the price we quote is the price you pay.</p>
    <p>For straightforward removals, we fell the tree in a controlled direction. For complex jobs near structures or in tight spaces, we use sectional cutting with rigging to lower pieces safely. Either way, we cut the trunk flush or grind the stump, haul away all debris, and leave your yard clean.</p>

    <h2>Tree Removal Costs in Concord</h2>
    <p>Pricing depends on the tree's size, location, and complexity:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Small trees (under 30 ft):</strong> $300 – $800</li>
      <li><strong>Medium trees (30–60 ft):</strong> $800 – $1,500</li>
      <li><strong>Large trees (60+ ft):</strong> $1,500 – $2,500+</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Technical removals near power lines or structures may be higher due to the additional rigging and safety precautions required.</p>
  `}
/>
